Deutonymph (
Figs. 6–7
). Dorsal shield divided into anterior and posterior plates; anterior dorsal plate subdivided into large anterior plate and pair of small posterolateral plates (
Fig. 6
). The anterior apex of coxal plates I wide and rounded (
Fig. 7
). I–L– 6 less than half as long as I–L– 5 , a pair of proximoventral setae on posterolateral surface of I–L– 6 inserted near midlength of segment.

